📍Forrest Gump Point
  Monument Valley, UTAH , USA

This is the place where Forrest Gump famously stopped after running coast to coast🏃🏻‍♂️A scene we all remember 🤠

ℹ️Forrest Gump Point is located in Mexican Hat, Utah within the beautiful Monument Valley 🏜️🌵

📍It is located on highway 163, about 16 miles from the Monument Valley Tribal Park 🏜️

🚗 Stay cautious while taking photos & watch out for cars as they drive fast from both directions

📸For the most dramatic photos, try for the golden hour (just after sunrise or just before sunset) when the light is soft and warm☀️

 📷 There are big queues and crowd on the highway on Forrest Gump point,so to avoid that you can even take pictures from “Monument Valley Scenic Outlook”🏜️ You get the same view from here and no crowd 🌄

📍Erthya Restaurant - Cupertino, California 

A restaurant where Indian flavors meet global influences in a beautifully modern setting🍛✨

Erthya reimagines traditional Indian dishes with a creative twist, blending heritage and innovation into every plate. From bold spices to refined techniques, it’s a dining experience that celebrates culture through a contemporary lens🍛🌮🍮

🍽️ Here’s what we ordered and enjoyed
🍹Drinks : Tota & Old fashioned
🌮Starters : Gol Gappa Surprise,Afgani Soya chaap,Palak chat,
Impossible Galouti,Teriyaki Bao
🍛Main course : Paneer Lazwab,Daal Makhani,Butter Naan
